  <preparation>BOUQUET GARNI:  thyme, bay leaf and parsley in cloth cheese bag or teaball.

Wash chicken and pat dry.  Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken with flour mixture.  

In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.  

Brown chicken in hot bacon drippings.  Push chicken aside; add onions and mushrooms and cook and stir until onions are tender.  

Drain off fat.

Crumble bacon; stir in with remaining ingredients.  Cover; simmer about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.  Remove Bouquet Garni before serving.  Skim off excess fat.  If desired, sprinkle with snipped parsley.  </preparation>
